summary:
The Monitoring Team's responsibilities include:
* Collating, assessing, monitoring, and reporting on implementation of measures (Annex I, (a));
* Submitting a comprehensive programme of work and reports to the Committee (Annex I, (b) and (c));
* Analyzing reports and information submitted by Member States (Annex I, (d));
* Working closely with the CTC's Counter-Terrorism Executive Directorate and the 1540 Committee's group of experts (Annex I, (e));
* Developing a plan to address non-compliance (Annex I, (f));
* Providing recommendations to assist Member States with implementation (Annex I, (g));
* Consulting with Member States (Annex I, (h) and (k));
* Encouraging submission of names for inclusion on the Consolidated List (Annex I, (i));
* Studying and reporting on the changing nature of the threat (Annex I, (j)). 
Decides to remain actively seized of the matter (para. 22).
The Monitoring Team is to: 
report to the Committee on its work, including visits to Member States and activities; 
assist the Committee in preparing assessments to the Council; 
fulfill other responsibilities identified by the Committee.

Annex II to resolution 1617 (2005) requires the Government of _______________ to provide information on individuals, groups, undertakings, and entities added to the 1267 Committee's Consolidated List. The information includes: 
- Whether names are added to visa lookout lists
- Visas denied
- Financial institutions notified
- Assets frozen
- Arms embargo bans implemented
- Attempts to purchase arms 
and additional information, if available,  for the listed individuals and entities.
